<section xml:id="dbc.db.acronym" remap="topic" userlevel="easy"
   xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
   xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
   xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
  <title>Utilize Alternative Descriptions in Acronyms</title>
  <info>
    <definitions definitionfile="defs.xml"/>
  </info>
  
  <section role="problem">
    <title>Problem</title>
    <para>You want to show your acronyms and their descriptions in a
      consistent way, independant from any output formats.</para>
  </section>
  <section role="solution">
    <title>Solution</title>
    <para>Use an <tag>acronym</tag> element and insert an <tag>alt</tag>
    element as shown in the following example:</para>
    <programlisting language="xml">&lt;para>
  The &lt;acronym>XML&lt;alt>eXtensible Markup Language&lt;/alt>&lt;/acronym>
  is used for...
&lt;/para></programlisting>
  </section>
  <section role="discussion">
    <title>Discussion</title>
    <para>
    </para>
  </section>
</section>
